Filter and Create Columns for Diabetes and Readmission

In[]:
# Ensure diagnosis columns are strings
df[['diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3']] = df[['diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3']].astype(str)

# Define diabetes code create flag
extra_diabetes_codes = {
    '401', '780', '428', 'V10', 'V58', '999', 'E905', '250.9', 'V70', 'V66', 'V63', 'V60',
    'V57', 'V56', 'V55', 'V54', 'V53', 'V51', 'V45', 'V43', 'V26', 'V25', 'V07', 'E909'
}
diabetes_codes = ['250'] + list(extra_diabetes_codes)
df[['diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3']] = df[['diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3']].astype(str)
df['diabetes_diag'] = (
    df['diag_1'].str.startswith('250') | df['diag_1'].isin(diabetes_codes) |
    df['diag_2'].str.startswith('250') | df['diag_2'].isin(diabetes_codes) |
    df['diag_3'].str.startswith('250') | df['diag_3'].isin(diabetes_codes)
).map({True: 'Yes', False: 'No'})
In[]:
# Create indicators and  Group Hospital utilization

#Create Glucose control indicator
df['glucose_control'] = (df['max_glu_serum'] .isin(['>200', '>300'])).astype(int)

# Create A1C tested indicator
df['a1c_tested'] = (df['A1Cresult'] != 'None').astype(int)

# Create High A1C indicator
df['a1c_high'] = (df['A1Cresult'] == '>8').astype(int)

# Calculate prior hospital utilization
df['prior_utilization'] = (df['number_outpatient'].astype(float) +
                           df['number_emergency'].astype(float) +
                           df['number_inpatient'].astype(float))

# Create medication change indicator
df['med_changed'] = (df['change'] == 'Ch').astype(int)

# Create polypharmacy indicator (>10 medications)
df['polypharmacy'] = (df['num_medications'].astype(float) > 10).astype(int)

# Create comorbidity burden indicator
df['high_comorbidity'] = (df['number_diagnoses'].astype(float) > 5).astype(int)

diabetic_df = df[df['diabetes_diag'] == 'Yes']

# Count diabetic patients with <30 or >30 readmission
readmitted_df = diabetic_df[diabetic_df['readmitted'].isin(['<30', '>30'])]
readmitted_count = len(readmitted_df)

# Calculate overall readmission rate
overall_readmit_rate = (readmitted_count / total_diabetic) * 100

print(f"Overall Diabetic Readmission Rate (excluding 'NO'): {overall_readmit_rate:.2f}%")

In[]:
#Average time in Hospital LOS

# Diabetic filter
diabetic_df = df[df['diabetes_diag'] == 'Yes']

# Average and percentage of all readmission categories among diabetics
readmission_counts = diabetic_df['readmitted'].value_counts()
readmission_percent = (readmission_counts / readmission_counts.sum()) * 100

# Combine into a summary table
summary_table = pd.DataFrame({
    'Count': readmission_counts,
    'Percentage': readmission_percent.round(2),
    'Avg_Time_in_Hospital': diabetic_df.groupby('readmitted')['time_in_hospital'].mean().round(2)
}).reset_index().rename(columns={'index': 'Readmission_Category'})

#  Total diabetic patients ---
total_diabetic_patients = diabetic_df.shape[0]

#summary table of average LOS per readmission category
print("Diabetic Readmission Summary (<30, >30, NO):")
print(f"{summary_table.to_string(float_format='%.2f%%')}")
print("\nTotal Diabetic Patients:", total_diabetic_patients)

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))
sns.barplot(
    data=summary_table,
    x='readmitted',
    y='Avg_Time_in_Hospital',
    palette = ('goldenrod', '#aeb4b5','#2e8be8')
)
plt.title('Average Length of Stay by Readmission Category (Diabetic Patients)')
plt.xlabel('readmitted')
plt.ylabel('Average Time in Hospital (Days)')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# Convert correlation matrix to pairs
corr_pairs = corr.unstack().reset_index()
corr_pairs.columns = ['Variable_1', 'Variable_2', 'Correlation']

# Remove duplicates (A-B same as B-A)
corr_pairs = corr_pairs[corr_pairs['Variable_1'] < corr_pairs['Variable_2']]

# Get absolute value to rank by strength
top_corrs = corr_pairs.reindex(corr_pairs['Correlation'].abs().sort_values(ascending=False).index)

# Show top 5 correlations
top5 = top_corrs.head(5)

# Utilization/Type of Admission

# Filter diabetic patients with <30 day readmission
diabetic_readmit_30 = df[(df['diabetes_diag'] == 'Yes') & (df['readmitted'] == '<30')]

# --- Totals (event-based sums) ---
sum_outpatient = diabetic_readmit_30['number_outpatient'].sum()
sum_emergency = diabetic_readmit_30['number_emergency'].sum()
sum_inpatient = diabetic_readmit_30['number_inpatient'].sum()

# --- Patient-based counts (1 visit of that type) ---
count_outpatient = (diabetic_readmit_30['number_outpatient'] > 0).sum()
count_emergency = (diabetic_readmit_30['number_emergency'] > 0).sum()
count_inpatient = (diabetic_readmit_30['number_inpatient'] > 0).sum()

# --- Total number of diabetic patients with <30-day readmission ---
total_patients = diabetic_readmit_30.shape[0]

# --- Combine into summary DataFrame ---
utilization_summary = pd.DataFrame({
    'Utilization Type': ['Outpatient', 'Emergency', 'Inpatient'],
    'Total Visits (Sum)': [sum_outpatient, sum_emergency, sum_inpatient],
    'Patients 1 Visit': [count_outpatient, count_emergency, count_inpatient]
})

# --- Add percentages ---
utilization_summary['% of Patients'] = (utilization_summary['Patients 1 Visit'] / total_patients * 100).round(2)
utilization_summary['% of Total Visits'] = (utilization_summary['Total Visits (Sum)'] / utilization_summary['Total Visits (Sum)'].sum() * 100).round(2)

# --- Display summary ---
print("Utilization Summary (Diabetic Patients with <30-Day Readmission)")
print(utilization_summary)
print(f"\nTotal Diabetic Patients with <30-Day Readmission: {total_patients}")


# Box plot
util_cols = ['number_outpatient', 'number_emergency', 'number_inpatient']

# Reshape to long format for seaborn

# Scale features
scaler = StandardScaler()

# Train-test split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)

# Fit logistic regression
model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, class_weight='balanced', random_state=42)
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Predict and evaluate
y_pred = model.predict(X_test)
y_prob = model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
report = classification_report(y_test, y_pred)
conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)

print(f"Accuracy: {acc:.2f}")
print("\nClassification Report:\n", report)
print("\nConfusion Matrix:\n", conf_matrix)
print(f"\nROC AUC Score: {roc_auc:.2f}")

fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)

import pandas as pd
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report, confusion_matrix, roc_auc_score, roc_curve
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Assuming df, diabetes_diag flag, and readmit_flag created as before

# Features used in model (same as logistic regression example)
features = [
    'time_in_hospital', 'num_lab_procedures', 'num_medications',
    'number_diagnoses', 'glucose_control', 'a1c_tested', 'a1c_high',
    'prior_utilization', 'med_changed', 'polypharmacy', 'high_comorbidity'
]

# Filter diabetic patients and drop missing values in selected features
df_model = df[df['diabetes_diag'] == 'Yes'].dropna(subset=features)
X = df_model[features]
y = df_model['readmit_flag']

# Scale features (optional for tree-based models but can be kept if you want uniformity)
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Train-test split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)

# Random Forest Classifier with balanced class weights
rf_model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100, class_weight='balanced', random_state=42)
rf_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred_rf = rf_model.predict(X_test)
y_prob_rf = rf_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

# Gradient Boosting Classifier (can use class_weight='balanced' via sample_weight)
gb_model = GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=100, learning_rate=0.1, random_state=42)
gb_model.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred_gb = gb_model.predict(X_test)
y_prob_gb = gb_model.predict_proba(X_test)[:, 1]

# Evaluation function for printing results and plotting ROC
def eval_model(y_test, y_pred, y_prob, model_name):
    acc = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred)
    report = classification_report(y_test, y_pred)
    conf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred)
    roc_auc = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_prob)

    print(f"\n{model_name} Results:")
    print(f"Accuracy: {acc:.2f}")
    print("\nClassification Report:\n", report)
    print("\nConfusion Matrix:\n", conf_matrix)
    print(f"\nROC AUC Score: {roc_auc:.2f}")

    fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y_test, y_prob)
    plt.plot(fpr, tpr, label=f'{model_name} (AUC = {roc_auc:.2f})')

plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6))

# Evaluate Random Forest
eval_model(y_test, y_pred_rf, y_prob_rf, 'Random Forest')

# Evaluate Gradient Boosting
eval_model(y_test, y_pred_gb, y_prob_gb, 'Gradient Boosting')

# Plot ROC baseline
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], linestyle='--', color='gray')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curves for Diabetic Readmission Prediction')
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# filter Dataset

df_30_full = df[df['diabetes_diag'] == 'Yes'].copy()
df_30_full['readmit_flag'] = (df_30_full['readmitted'] == '<30').astype(int)


numeric_features = [
    'time_in_hospital', 'num_lab_procedures', 'num_medications',
    'number_diagnoses', 'glucose_control', 'a1c_tested', 'a1c_high',
    'prior_utilization', 'med_changed', 'polypharmacy', 'high_comorbidity'
]

# Drop NAs
df_30_full = df_30_full.dropna(subset=numeric_features)

X = df_30_full[numeric_features]
y = df_30_full['readmit_flag']

# Scale features for stability
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)

# Split
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.3, random_state=42)

# Logistic model
lr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000, class_weight='balanced', random_state=42)
lr.fit(X_train, y_train)

# Risk probabilities
df_30_full['Risk_Score'] = lr.predict_proba(scaler.transform(X))[:, 1]

# Risk Levels
def risk_level(x):
    if x >= 0.7:
        return 'High'
    elif x >= 0.4:
        return 'Moderate'
    else:
        return 'Low'

df_30_full['Risk_Level'] = df_30_full['Risk_Score'].apply(risk_level)


print("Training set size:", X_train.shape)
print("Test set size:", X_test.shape)


plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
sns.histplot(data=df_30_full, x='Risk_Score', hue='Risk_Level', kde=True, palette='coolwarm')
plt.title('Distribution of Readmission Risk Scores')
plt.xlabel('Predicted Readmission Probability')
plt.ylabel('Patient Count')
plt.show()

    Write notebook output to stdout instead of files.
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.writer_class=StdoutWriter]
--inplace
    Run nbconvert in place, overwriting the existing notebook (only
            relevant when converting to notebook format)
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.use_output_suffix=False --NbConvertApp.export_format=notebook --FilesWriter.build_directory=]
--clear-output
    Clear output of current file and save in place,
            overwriting the existing notebook.
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.use_output_suffix=False --NbConvertApp.export_format=notebook --FilesWriter.build_directory= --ClearOutputPreprocessor.enabled=True]
--coalesce-streams
    Coalesce consecutive stdout and stderr outputs into one stream (within each cell).
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.use_output_suffix=False --NbConvertApp.export_format=notebook --FilesWriter.build_directory= --CoalesceStreamsPreprocessor.enabled=True]
--no-prompt
    Exclude input and output prompts from converted document.
    Equivalent to: [--TemplateExporter.exclude_input_prompt=True --TemplateExporter.exclude_output_prompt=True]
--no-input
    Exclude input cells and output prompts from converted document.
            This mode is ideal for generating code-free reports.
    Equivalent to: [--TemplateExporter.exclude_output_prompt=True --TemplateExporter.exclude_input=True --TemplateExporter.exclude_input_prompt=True]
--allow-chromium-download
    Whether to allow downloading chromium if no suitable version is found on the system.
    Equivalent to: [--WebPDFExporter.allow_chromium_download=True]
--disable-chromium-sandbox
    Disable chromium security sandbox when converting to PDF..
    Equivalent to: [--WebPDFExporter.disable_sandbox=True]
--show-input
    Shows code input. This flag is only useful for dejavu users.
    Equivalent to: [--TemplateExporter.exclude_input=False]
--embed-images
    Embed the images as base64 dataurls in the output. This flag is only useful for the HTML/WebPDF/Slides exports.
    Equivalent to: [--HTMLExporter.embed_images=True]
--sanitize-html
    Whether the HTML in Markdown cells and cell outputs should be sanitized..
    Equivalent to: [--HTMLExporter.sanitize_html=True]
--log-level=<Enum>
    Set the log level by value or name.
    Choices: any of [0, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 'DEBUG', 'INFO', 'WARN', 'ERROR', 'CRITICAL']
    Default: 30
    Equivalent to: [--Application.log_level]
--config=<Unicode>
    Full path of a config file.
    Default: ''
    Equivalent to: [--JupyterApp.config_file]
--to=<Unicode>
    The export format to be used, either one of the built-in formats
            ['asciidoc', 'custom', 'html', 'latex', 'markdown', 'notebook', 'pdf', 'python', 'qtpdf', 'qtpng', 'rst', 'script', 'slides', 'webpdf']
            or a dotted object name that represents the import path for an
            ``Exporter`` class
    Default: ''
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.export_format]
--template=<Unicode>
    Name of the template to use
    Default: ''
    Equivalent to: [--TemplateExporter.template_name]
--template-file=<Unicode>
    Name of the template file to use
    Default: None
    Equivalent to: [--TemplateExporter.template_file]
--theme=<Unicode>
    Template specific theme(e.g. the name of a JupyterLab CSS theme distributed
    as prebuilt extension for the lab template)
    Default: 'light'
    Equivalent to: [--HTMLExporter.theme]
--sanitize_html=<Bool>
    Whether the HTML in Markdown cells and cell outputs should be sanitized.This
    should be set to True by nbviewer or similar tools.
    Default: False
    Equivalent to: [--HTMLExporter.sanitize_html]
--writer=<DottedObjectName>
    Writer class used to write the
                                        results of the conversion
    Default: 'FilesWriter'
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.writer_class]
--post=<DottedOrNone>
    PostProcessor class used to write the
                                        results of the conversion
    Default: ''
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.postprocessor_class]
--output=<Unicode>
    Overwrite base name use for output files.
                Supports pattern replacements '{notebook_name}'.
    Default: '{notebook_name}'
    Equivalent to: [--NbConvertApp.output_base]
--output-dir=<Unicode>
    Directory to write output(s) to. Defaults
                                  to output to the directory of each notebook. To recover
                                  previous default behaviour (outputting to the current
                                  working directory) use . as the flag value.
    Default: ''
    Equivalent to: [--FilesWriter.build_directory]
--reveal-prefix=<Unicode>
    The URL prefix for reveal.js (version 3.x).
            This defaults to the reveal CDN, but can be any url pointing to a copy
            of reveal.js.
            For speaker notes to work, this must be a relative path to a local
            copy of reveal.js: e.g., "reveal.js".
            If a relative path is given, it must be a subdirectory of the
            current directory (from which the server is run).
            See the usage documentation
            (https://nbconvert.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usage.html#reveal-js-html-slideshow)
            for more details.
    Default: ''
    Equivalent to: [--SlidesExporter.reveal_url_prefix]
--nbformat=<Enum>
    The nbformat version to write.
            Use this to downgrade notebooks.
    Choices: any of [1, 2, 3, 4]
    Default: 4
    Equivalent to: [--NotebookExporter.nbformat_version]

Examples
--------

    The simplest way to use nbconvert is

            > jupyter nbconvert mynotebook.ipynb --to html

            Options include ['asciidoc', 'custom', 'html', 'latex', 'markdown', 'notebook', 'pdf', 'python', 'qtpdf', 'qtpng', 'rst', 'script', 'slides', 'webpdf'].

            > jupyter nbconvert --to latex mynotebook.ipynb

            Both HTML and LaTeX support multiple output templates. LaTeX includes
            'base', 'article' and 'report'.  HTML includes 'basic', 'lab' and
            'classic'. You can specify the flavor of the format used.

            > jupyter nbconvert --to html --template lab mynotebook.ipynb

            You can also pipe the output to stdout, rather than a file

            > jupyter nbconvert mynotebook.ipynb --stdout

            PDF is generated via latex

            > jupyter nbconvert mynotebook.ipynb --to pdf

            You can get (and serve) a Reveal.js-powered slideshow

            > jupyter nbconvert myslides.ipynb --to slides --post serve

            Multiple notebooks can be given at the command line in a couple of
            different ways:

            > jupyter nbconvert notebook*.ipynb
            > jupyter nbconvert notebook1.ipynb notebook2.ipynb

            or you can specify the notebooks list in a config file, containing::

                c.NbConvertApp.notebooks = ["my_notebook.ipynb"]

            > jupyter nbconvert --config mycfg.py

To see all available configurables, use `--help-all`.
